body.description: This is a single pack of an orthodontic 0 to 6 month pacifier. Ecopiggy Ecopacifier is the preferred natural rubber pacifier. Sustainably made from 100% natural rubber, from the tree Hevea Brasiliensis, ecopacifier is softer and more natural than artificial silicone. Our round shield lightly touches the child's nose, simulating the soothing feel of breast feeding. Ecopacifier's single-piece design ensures no small pieces to gather dirt and germs, and no small pieces means no choking hazards. Ecopiggy natural rubber pacifiers are made without chemical softeners or colorants, and are BPA-Free, Phthalate-Free, PVC-Free, and Paraben-Free. Children love the natural soothing effects of Ecopacifier, offered in two styles; Orthodontic and Rounded. Due to the soft quality of Ecopacifier, our natural rubber pacifier will not leave marks on your child's face. Child happy. Parents happy. Ecopiggy's Natural Pacifier, Ecopacifier, is made of 100% pure rubber from the rubber tree, Hevea brasillensi. These trees are sustainably grown in plantations in Malaysia. The rubber tree exudes a latex sap, the world’s primary source of natural rubber, which is tapped in a similar manner to maple syrup from a maple tree. After about 20-25 years the tree stops producing latex sap. The trees are then harvested and replanted. The harvested wood is used extensively in furniture, flooring, construction and even toys. From seed to tree to ecopacifier to wooden toys, the Rubbertree has an eco-friendly, sustainable and high quality life. Ecopacifier is sustainably made in Malaysia. Ecopiggy is committed to offering the highest quality, natural products. We feel it's equally important to think of the overall footprint when manufacturing products, so we manufacturing our natural rubber pacifiers right at the source of natural rubber! They ship consolidated, and are once again hand-inspected and packaged in the USA. Happy Earth. Happy Families.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is the 3rd one we have had with 2 kids who liked them. We did try the other circular one same brand and both kids did not like the round tip. We like the flat end better.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best rubber nunu.
reviews.reviewText: Best pacis ever. It smelled strongly of rubber in the beginning but after that wore off, this thing became our lifesaver.Fast forward TWO YEARS and our 2 year old still uses his same newborn paci. All in all, we have 2 ecopiggy nunus and they have held up all this time. I find we tend to keep track of them better too since they are on the pricier side.We also purchased the natersutten paci at one point when we thought we lost one and it wasnt nearly as good. The quality of ecopiggy exceeds the other brands for sure. It's the only thing we'll use now.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Baby Loves Them
reviews.reviewText: First I want to start off by saying that my baby loves them. She won’t take any others. The only thing that sucks about this product is that it’s natural rubber deteriorates over time. It’s only suggested 4-6 weeks use which is a bummer to have to buy a $12-$14 pacifier every month. I wish I had known that from the beginning and I wouldn’t have introduced her to them. But now she’s hooked so I guess it’ll be a monthly purchase. Great for baby but not great for my wallet.The smell has a little intense rubber smell and I would assume that would bother her but it doesn’t. It bothers me but again, it’s for baby and not for me.All in all, I’m glad I found something she loves and uses constantly. She’s just bougie, is all, with her fancy, expensive pacifiers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 2, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth the money!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 9, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for a one piece pacifier that would not not retain water, had a comfortable nipple for my daughter, and also a neutral color. After sanitizing this upon arrival, I offered it to my 3 month old and she accepted it. She has been using it for a couple days now and seems to like it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Wrong sized product, might as well have sent me an empty box, would have been just as helpful.
reviews.reviewText: I ordered a 0-6 month pacifier and was sent a 6 month and up. I already have the 6 month pacifier (a gift) and it's too big, hence why I ordered a smaller size for my 3 month old. Also, tomorrow I am traveling on a plane and now I'm in a predicament. Unbelievable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 14, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Great product, but make sure you change frequently!
reviews.reviewText: My son loved this pacifier, until the tip broke off out of nowhere, thankfully not while it was in his mouth. We had 2 of these, and even the second one that had not broken had lines where you could tell it was worn and could break at any time. I contacted the company, but received no response. After reading the box, it states to change the pacifier every 6-8 weeks (which of course we hadn't, it had been 5 months with 2 pacifiers) so apparently natural rubber isn't the strongest material.
Buenísimo chupon. Mi bebé lo amó.
